plotText.plainText: A young Viking prince is on a quest to avenge his father's murder.

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise in Collateral (2004)

plotText.plainText: A cab driver finds himself the hostage of an engaging contract killer as he makes his rounds from hit to hit during one night in Los Angeles.

caption.plainText: Nick Frost and Simon Pegg in Hot Fuzz (2007)

plotText.plainText: An overachieving London police sergeant is transferred to a village where the easygoing officers object to his fervor for regulations, all while a string of grisly murders strikes the town.

caption.plainText: Jim Carrey in The Truman Show (1998)

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise in Mission: Impossible II (2000)

plotText.plainText: IMF agent Ethan Hunt is sent to Sydney to find and destroy a genetically modified disease called "Chimera".

caption.plainText: Mission: Impossible (1996)

plotText.plainText: An American agent, under false suspicion of disloyalty, must discover and expose the real spy without the help of his organization.

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise in Mission: Impossible III (2006)

plotText.plainText: IMF agent Ethan Hunt comes into conflict with a dangerous and sadistic arms dealer who threatens his life and his fiancée in response.

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise, Alec Baldwin, Ving Rhames, Rebecca Ferguson, Simon Pegg, and Jeremy Renner in Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation (2015)

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise, Alec Baldwin, Angela Bassett, Ving Rhames, Henry Cavill, Rebecca Ferguson, and Simon Pegg in Mission: Impossible - Fallout (2018)

plotText.plainText: A group of terrorists plans to detonate three plutonium cores for a simultaneous nuclear attack on different cities. Ethan Hunt, along with his IMF team, sets out to stop the carnage.

caption.plainText: Leonardo DiCaprio, Kate Winslet, Billy Zane, Kathy Bates, and Frances Fisher in Titanic (1997)

plotText.plainText: A seventeen-year-old aristocrat falls in love with a kind but poor artist aboard the luxurious, ill-fated R.M.S. Titanic.

caption.plainText: John David Washington in Tenet (2020)

plotText.plainText: Armed with only the word "Tenet," and fighting for the survival of the entire world, CIA operative, The Protagonist, journeys through a twilight world of international espionage on a global mission that unfolds beyond real time.

caption.plainText: Fionn Whitehead in Dunkirk (2017)

plotText.plainText: Allied soldiers from Belgium, the British Commonwealth and Empire, and France are surrounded by the German Army and evacuated during a fierce battle in World War II.

caption.plainText: Leonardo DiCaprio in The Revenant (2015)

plotText.plainText: A frontiersman on a fur trading expedition in the 1820s fights for survival after being mauled by a bear and left for dead by members of his own hunting team.

caption.plainText: Matt Damon in The Martian - Strandet på Mars (2015)

plotText.plainText: An astronaut becomes stranded on Mars after his team assume him dead, and must rely on his ingenuity to find a way to signal to Earth that he is alive and can survive until a potential rescue.

caption.plainText: The Trial of the Chicago 7 (2020)

plotText.plainText: The story of 7 people on trial stemming from various charges surrounding the uprising at the 1968 Democratic National Convention in Chicago, Illinois.

caption.plainText: Sylvester Stallone and Michael B. Jordan in Creed (2015)

plotText.plainText: The former World Heavyweight Champion Rocky Balboa serves as a trainer and mentor to Adonis Johnson, the son of his late friend and former rival Apollo Creed.

caption.plainText: Neil Brown Jr., Aldis Hodge, Corey Hawkins, Jason Mitchell, and O'Shea Jackson Jr. in Straight Outta Compton (2015)

plotText.plainText: The rap group NWA emerges from the mean streets of Compton in the mid-1980s and revolutionizes hip-hop culture with their music and tales about life in the hood.

caption.plainText: Kevin Spacey, Jamie Foxx, Jon Hamm, Eiza González, Lily James, and Ansel Elgort in Baby Driver (2017)

plotText.plainText: Doc forces Baby, a former getaway driver, to partake in a heist, threatening to hurt his girlfriend if he refuses. But the plan goes awry when their arms dealers turn out to be undercover officers.

caption.plainText: Ian McKellen, Richard Armitage, Jed Brophy, John Callen, Martin Freeman, Mark Hadlow, Peter Hambleton, William Kircher, Graham McTavish, James Nesbitt, Dean O'Gorman, Ken Stott, Stephen Hunter, Aidan Turner, and Adam Brown in Hobbiten: En uventet reise (2012)

plotText.plainText: A reluctant Hobbit, Bilbo Baggins, sets out to the Lonely Mountain with a spirited group of dwarves to reclaim their mountain home and the gold within it from the dragon Smaug.

originalTitleText.text: The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies

caption.plainText: Martin Freeman in Hobbiten: Femhærerslaget (2014)

caption.plainText: Matt Damon and Danny DeVito in Regnmakeren (1997)

plotText.plainText: An underdog lawyer takes on a fraudulent insurance company.

caption.plainText: Russell Crowe and Denzel Washington in American Gangster (2007)

plotText.plainText: An outcast New York City cop is charged with bringing down Harlem drug lord Frank Lucas, whose real life inspired this partly biographical film.

caption.plainText: Matt Damon, Franka Potente, and Nicky Naudé in Hvem var Jason Bourne (2002)

plotText.plainText: A man is picked up by a fishing boat, bullet-riddled and suffering from amnesia, before racing to elude assassins and attempting to regain his memory.

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise in Oblivion (2013)

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise and Emily Blunt in Edge of Tomorrow (2014)

plotText.plainText: A soldier fighting aliens gets to relive the same day over and over again, the day restarting every time he dies.

caption.plainText: Jesse Eisenberg in The Social Network (2010)

plotText.plainText: As Harvard student Mark Zuckerberg creates the social networking site that would become known as Facebook, he is sued by the twins who claimed he stole their idea and by the co-founder who was later squeezed out of the business.

caption.plainText: Zodiac (2007)

caption.plainText: Helena Bonham Carter, Henry Cavill, Susan Wokoma, Adeel Akhtar, Sam Claflin, Millie Bobby Brown, and Louis Partridge in Enola Holmes (2020)

plotText.plainText: When Enola Holmes, Sherlock's sister, discovers her mother is missing, she endeavors to find her, becoming a super-sleuth in her own right as she outwits her famous brother and unravels a dangerous conspiracy.

caption.plainText: Samuel L. Jackson and Clyde Goins in Coach Carter (2005)

plotText.plainText: Controversy surrounds high school basketball coach Ken Carter after he benches his entire team for breaking their academic contract with him.

plotText.plainText: In the early 1960s, CIA agent Napoleon Solo and KGB operative Illya Kuryakin participate in a joint mission against a mysterious criminal organization, which is working to proliferate nuclear weapons.

caption.plainText: Brad Pitt, Christian Bale, Steve Carell, and Ryan Gosling in The Big Short (2015)

plotText.plainText: In 2006-2007 a group of investors bet against the United States mortgage market. In their research, they discover how flawed and corrupt the market is.

caption.plainText: Brad Pitt in Moneyball (2011)

plotText.plainText: Oakland A's general manager Billy Beane's successful attempt to assemble a baseball team on a lean budget by employing computer-generated analysis to acquire new players.

caption.plainText: Brad Pitt in World War Z (2013)

plotText.plainText: Former United Nations employee Gerry Lane traverses the world in a race against time to stop a zombie pandemic that is toppling armies and governments and threatens to destroy humanity itself.

caption.plainText: Osric Chau in 2012 (2009)

plotText.plainText: A frustrated writer struggles to keep his family alive when a series of global catastrophes threatens to annihilate mankind.

caption.plainText: Gravity (2013)

plotText.plainText: Dr Ryan Stone, an engineer on her first time on a space mission, and Matt Kowalski, an astronaut on his final expedition, have to survive in space after they are hit by debris while spacewalking.

caption.plainText: Robert De Niro, Al Pacino, and Joe Pesci in The Irishman (2019)

plotText.plainText: An illustration of Frank Sheeran's life, from W.W.II veteran to hit-man for the Bufalino crime family and his alleged assassination of his close friend Jimmy Hoffa.

caption.plainText: Tom Hanks and Audrey Tautou in Da Vinci-koden (2006)

plotText.plainText: A murder inside the Louvre, and clues in Da Vinci paintings, lead to the discovery of a religious mystery protected by a secret society for two thousand years, which could shake the foundations of Christianity.

caption.plainText: Tom Hanks and Felicity Jones in Inferno (2016)

plotText.plainText: When Robert Langdon wakes up in an Italian hospital with amnesia, he teams up with Dr. Sienna Brooks and they race across Europe together against the clock to foil a deadly global plot.

caption.plainText: Michael Keaton, Liev Schreiber, Brian d'Arcy James, Mark Ruffalo, and Rachel McAdams in Spotlight (2015)

plotText.plainText: The true story of how the Boston Globe uncovered the massive scandal of child molestation and cover-up within the local Catholic Archdiocese, shaking the entire Catholic Church to its core.

caption.plainText: Ben Affleck in Gone Girl (2014)

plotText.plainText: With his wife's disappearance having become the focus of an intense media circus, a man sees the spotlight turned on him when it's suspected that he may not be innocent.

caption.plainText: Javier Bardem and Josh Brolin in No Country for Old Men (2007)

plotText.plainText: Violence and mayhem ensue after a hunter stumbles upon the aftermath of a drug deal gone wrong and over two million dollars in cash near the Rio Grande.

caption.plainText: Haley Joel Osment in Den sjette sansen (1999)

plotText.plainText: Malcolm Crowe, a child psychologist, starts treating a young boy, Cole, who encounters dead people and convinces him to help them. In turn, Cole helps Malcolm reconcile with his estranged wife.

caption.plainText: Tom Cruise in Top Gun: Maverick (2022)

plotText.plainText: The story involves Maverick confronting his past while training a group of younger Top Gun graduates, including the son of his deceased best friend, for a dangerous mission.

caption.plainText: Robert De Niro in Taxisjåføren (1976)

plotText.plainText: A mentally unstable veteran works as a nighttime taxi driver in New York City, where the perceived decadence and sleaze fuels his urge for violent action.

plotText.plainText: A group of high-end professional thieves start to feel the heat from the LAPD when they unknowingly leave a verbal clue at their latest heist.

caption.plainText: Oldboy (2003)

plotText.plainText: After being kidnapped and imprisoned for fifteen years, Oh Dae-Su is released, only to find that he must track down his captor in five days.

caption.plainText: Song Kang-ho, Jung Ik-han, Jung Hyun-jun, Lee Joo-hyung, Lee Ji-hye, Lee Sun-kyun, Cho Yeo-jeong, Park Myeong-hoon, Park Keun-rok, Jang Hye-jin, Lee Jeong-eun, Choi Woo-sik, Park Seo-joon, Park So-dam, and Jung Ji-so in Parasitt (2019)

plotText.plainText: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

plotText.plainText: 12-year-old Mathilda is reluctantly taken in by Léon, a professional assassin, after her family is murdered. An unusual relationship forms as she becomes his protégée and learns the assassin's trade.

caption.plainText: Jodie Foster in Nattsvermeren (1991)

plotText.plainText: A young F.B.I. cadet must receive the help of an incarcerated and manipulative cannibal killer to help catch another serial killer, a madman who skins his victims.

caption.plainText: Henry Fonda, Martin Balsam, Jack Klugman, Lee J. Cobb, Ed Begley, Edward Binns, John Fiedler, E.G. Marshall, Joseph Sweeney, George Voskovec, Jack Warden, and Robert Webber in 12 edsvorne menn (1957)

plotText.plainText: The jury in a New York City murder trial is frustrated by a single member whose skeptical caution forces them to more carefully consider the evidence before jumping to a hasty verdict.

caption.plainText: François Cluzet and Omar Sy in De urørlige (2011)

plotText.plainText: After he becomes a quadriplegic from a paragliding accident, an aristocrat hires a young man from the projects to be his caregiver.
